body:
I narrowed down the issue to:
```python
def func(parameter):
    if tuple() + (parameter[1],) in set():
        raise Exception()
```

Going to see if I can find a solution, but someone might know what's up with this!

@DanielNoord The issue is caused by https://github.com/PyCQA/astroid/pull/979. `Unknown` doesn't have a `AsStringVisitor`, thus [astroid -> _to_literal](https://github.com/PyCQA/astroid/blob/5b516c9001fad3a8060c956821fb8f81f156c961/astroid/inference.py#L811-L814) will fail. It doesn't really make sense to add one either, since the node is `Unknown`. What should the return string be in that case?

Instead, I would recommend to add `AttributeError` to the list of exceptions [here](https://github.com/PyCQA/astroid/blob/5b516c9001fad3a8060c956821fb8f81f156c961/astroid/inference.py#L841-L845) and add a comment [here](https://github.com/PyCQA/astroid/blob/5b516c9001fad3a8060c956821fb8f81f156c961/astroid/inference.py#L812-L813) to explain that it can also raise `AttributeError`, since not all nodes do have a visitor.
@DanielNoord Would you like to prepare the PR? I can do the review if you link me.
Yeah sure! Will probably do that tomorrow if that's okay?

> Yeah sure! Will probably do that tomorrow if that's okay?

No problem. Thanks!
